    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change column width of mui table in React js, you can use this css code . It will change column width of mui table‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change column width of mui table in React js, you can use this css code <code class=\"language-text\">width=\"100\"</code>. It will change column width of mui table.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change column width of mui table in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install Material-UI.</li>\n<li>Import the Mui table component.</li>\n<li>Set Column Width.</li>\n<li>Define the Mui table component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install Material-UI</h3>\n<p>The first step is to install Material-UI. And you can use npm or yarn. And you can open it by typing in terminal.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import the Mui table component.</h3>\n<p>To change column width of mui table in React, first, you have to import the table. We have imported the <code class=\"language-text\">Table</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">TableBody</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">TableCell</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">TableHead</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">TableRow</code> components from the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> library.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Table<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableBody<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableCell<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableHead<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableRow <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Set Column Width.</h3>\n<p>To change the column width of a Material-UI table, you can use the width property of the tablecell component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 4: Define the Mui table component.</h3>\n<p>We have to define to show the data of our table. we will create an array of employees with their Column 1, Column 2, and Column 3.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableHead<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableHead<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>MUI material change column width of mui table example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a Material UI table. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">@mui material</code> table. In the Material Table function when you create a table component, it consists of a table head and a table body. This code sets the width property of each TableCell component to a fixed value. </p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Table<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableBody<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableCell<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableHead<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TableRow <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">CustomTable</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Table<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableHead<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Column <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableHead<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableBody<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Row <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Column <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableCell<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableRow<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>TableBody<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Table<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and changed column width of mui table.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/ec897/column-width.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 18.354430379746837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRkYAAABXRUJQVlA4IDoAAAAwAwCdASoUAAQAPtFUo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJZwAAW+s3CbAAAP7wG65BaYWcwX0ClDjkfRLP1/J9CRgA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, column, width\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, column, width\"\n        src=\"/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/8aab1/column-width.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/81b7c/column-width.webp 158w,\n/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/6ea66/column-width.webp 315w,\n/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/8aab1/column-width.webp 630w,\n/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/a70f5/column-width.webp 945w,\n/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/4ef06/column-width.webp 1260w,\n/static/3ee0b4390da4e2b920e80ea5f43c5fee/ec897/column-width.webp 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolut